---
name: rest-validate
---

# v1.5 Tier 5 #20 — `validate { … }` accumulator + `requireRange`

```scalascript
// Fake request: anything with `.form` / `.query` Map fields plays the
// role.  WebServer / route() construct the same shape — the helpers
// just look up by name through `.form ?? .query`.
case class FakeReq(form: Map[String, String], query: Map[String, String])

val ok      = FakeReq(Map("email" -> "ada@example.com", "rating" -> "4"), Map())
val bad     = FakeReq(Map("email" -> "x",                "rating" -> "9"), Map())
val missing = FakeReq(Map(),                                              Map())

// Happy path — no errors, returns Right with the body's value.
val r1 = validate {
  val email  = requireString(ok, "email")
  val rating = requireRange(ok, "rating", 1, 5)
  (email, rating)
}
println(r1)

// Range violation accumulated with the rest.
val r2 = validate {
  val email  = requireString(bad, "email")
  val rating = requireRange(bad, "rating", 1, 5)
  (email, rating)
}
println(r2)

// Missing fields accumulate too — all problems in one pass.
val r3 = validate {
  val email  = requireString(missing, "email")
  val rating = requireRange(missing, "rating", 1, 5)
  val tone   = requireOneOf(missing, "tone", List("info", "warn"))
  (email, rating, tone)
}
println(r3)

// requireRangeDouble.
val ok2 = FakeReq(Map("score" -> "0.75"), Map())
val r4  = validate { requireRangeDouble(ok2, "score", 0.0, 1.0) }
println(r4)

val bad2 = FakeReq(Map("score" -> "1.5"), Map())
val r5   = validate { requireRangeDouble(bad2, "score", 0.0, 1.0) }
println(r5)
```
